    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith ui2 enabled and `cmdheight=0` pressing `<CR>` during `vim.fn.getchar()` might switch focus to command line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following 'init.lua':\n\n    ```lua\n    vim.o.cmdheight = 0\n    require('vim._core.ui2').enable({ enable = true })\n\n    local echo_and_getchar = function()\n      vim.api.nvim_echo({ { 'Hello' } }, false, {})\n      return vim.fn.getchar()\n    end\n    vim.keymap.set('n', '<M-m>', echo_and_getchar)\n    ```\n\n2. `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n3. Press `<M-m>` to initiate the code and press `<CR>`. Focus is switched to the command line (I believe as a result of \"enter the pager\" assumption, but not sure) even though `<CR>` is meant to only be consumed by `getchar()`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing any key when `getchar()` is active should not have side effects.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-601+gd214c24129\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 7.0.9-arch2-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, UI2 is using a vim.on_key() handler to enter the pager with <CR>. There doesn't seem to be a way to detect that this key is/should be consumed by an active getchar().",
