            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Yes, UI2 is using a vim.on_key() handler to enter the pager with . There doesn't seem to be a way to detect that this key is/should be consumed by an active getchar().\n\nI don't think there is one either.\n\nIt was a small surprise to see this behavior, as I don't really know if that is expected. There is an explicit `g<` to enter the special buffer to navigate through messages. Is `<CR>` really needed here? As it seems to be problematic to reliably detect `ENTER immediately after interactive |:| cmdline shows a message and returns to |Normal-mode|`.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-26T13:28:18Z",
