            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> using a vim.on_key() handler to enter the pager with . There doesn't seem to be a way to detect that this key is/should be consumed by an active getchar().\n\nCan we enhance `on_key` somehow?\n\n> Is `<CR>` really needed here?\n\nIt's a compromise to mollify the people that will (and did already) inevitably complain about having to use `g<`, since they are used to the old non-UI2 behavior.",
