            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Can we enhance on_key somehow?\n\nJust not doing `on_key` callbacks during getchar() would \"solve\" this problem, but IDK if that should be the expected behavior. It seems somewhat logical to not allow `on_key` listeners to hijack getchar() calls.\n\nOther options are an argument to the callback indicating this state, or a UI event as suggested in #20311.",
